President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Karol V. Mason as Assistant Attorney General for Justice Programs at the Department of Justice. Mason is currently a partner at the law firm of Alston & Bird, LLP and previously served as Deputy Associate Attorney General at the U.S. Department of Justice. She has extensive experience in the legal field and has received several awards for her service. 

Additionally, President Obama has announced his intent to appoint Catherine A. Allen as a member of the Board of Directors of the Valles Caldera Trust. Allen is the Chairman and CEO of the Santa Fe Group and has a background in strategic consulting. She has held various positions in the financial services industry and currently serves on multiple boards of directors. Allen has also received recognition for her achievements, including a Lifetime Achievement Award from U.S. Banker Magazine.